f(x)=p
f(x+kp)
f(x)+Kp
K
p \mid f(x) \Rightarrow p \mid (f(x)+kP)
f(x+kp)
(x+kp)^n
\alpha_n
 (x+kp)^n = x^n + {n \choose 1} x^{n-1} k p + {n \choose 2} x^{n-2} k^2 p^2 + \cdots \\ = x^n + \alpha_n p \text{ where $\alpha_n$ is an integer} 
 f(x+kp) = a_n (x^n + \alpha_n p) + a_{n-1} (x^{n-1} + \alpha_{n-1} p) \cdot \\=  a_n x^n + a_{n-1} x^{n-1} + \cdots + (a_n \alpha_n + a_{n-1} \alpha_{n-1}+\cdots) p\\ =f(x) + K p 
